               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1434" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1434" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1434" type="surname" value="STEVENS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1434" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE STEVENS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a plumber, and live in Bermondsey-street—the prisoner was in my service for about fifteen months—on the 9th of February, early in the morning, I received information, I got up and saw a pig of lead standing in the passage by the side of my house—I waited and saw the prisoner come and take it up, and go off with it—be had no business with it—he was sent with another to clean the windows of the Deaf and Dumb Asylum—I followed, and when I came up to him be put it down and ran away—I secured, and took him to the shop, and he begged for mercy.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How far had he carried it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About twenty yards—he asked me to forgive him for the sake of his family—he has a wife and eight children—he ran sixty or seventy yards—I had bought this pig of lead—I had twenty-nine in the shop.</p>
               <p>
